    "detected_at": "2026-02-08T09:57:00+00:00",
    "resolved_at": "2026-02-08T10:44:00+00:00",
    "title": "Checkout failure cascade from orders DB pool exhaustion",
    "severity": "high",
    "summary": "Orders service deployment d1a7f3c shipped a query change that added a JOIN to the order-line lookup, doubling per-request DB time. Connections held longer; the shared Postgres pool (max=120 across orders, inventory, notifications) saturated at 09:54. Inventory and notifications were the first to surface the symptom because their connection-acquire timeout was 2s vs orders' 8s. Checkout success rate fell from 99% to 61% over three minutes. Rollback to the prior query at 10:42 restored normal pool utilization within 2 minutes.\n",
    "affected_services": [
      "orders",
      "inventory",
      "notifications"
    ]
  },
